x^3\frac{dy}{dx}+3x^2y=x^5y^2
z=x^3y,\frac{dz}{dx}=x^3\frac{dy}{dx}+3x^2y
\frac{dz}{dx}=\frac{z^2}{x}
\frac{dz}{z^2}=\frac{dx}x
-\frac1z=\ln x+c
z=\frac1{c_1-\ln x}
y=\frac1{x^3(c_1-\ln x)}
